HTTP                                    HTTPS:
1. HTTP is unsecured                    HTTPS is secured
2. HTTP sends data over port 80         HTTPS uses port 443

3. HTTP operates at application layer   HTTPS operates at transport layer
4. No SSL certificates are required     HTTPS it is required that you have an SSL certificate
for HTTP                                and it is signed by a CA.

5. HTTP doesn't require domain          HTTPS requires at least domain validation and certain certificates
validation                              even require legal document validation
6. No encryption in HTTP                HTTPS the data is encrypted before sending.


